    "title": "Pre/postTasksExecution on neither main or Nx Agents",
    "description": "@caleb said:\n\n> Got a question from Payfit that I'd like some clarification on for the `preTasksExecution` and `postTasksExecution` api w/ Nx Agents.\n>\n> We noticed that when running with Nx Agents the `postTasksExeuction` is not called on the agent machines nor the main job. `preTasksExecution` is called on the main job.\n> when running with `--no-agents` then things are all called on the main job. which is expected.\n> My main question is what is expected behavior, pre/post called on agents, or pre/post called on main job. or pre/post called across main/agents jobs\n> any reason why post isn't being called today? (I presume bug but wanted to double check first). Happy to write some docs on the behavior once we know what's supposed to happen.\n>\n> cc @jason @altan",
