    "description": "This might be kind of insane. But can Nx track which tasks are \"Running\" on disk… so that other Nx commands can see \"Oh hey, that's already running, I don't need to run it.\" This way, we can continue to run `nx serve app` in Playwright, Cypress, or Jest…. and if one is already running… we won't run another one. And…. this would make re-running e2e tests seamless if the user already has their dev server running. Cypress and Playwright will just magically reuse the existing servers.",
