    "title": "Investigate Cypress inferred target plugins for component testing",
    "description": "@caleb said:\n\n> About to jump on a plane so can’t double check some of this info. But do we have an example of component testing with the cypress inferred target plugins? \n> [https://nrwl.slack.com/archives/C06HQ9TKL10/p1736962346283219](https://nrwl.slack.com/archives/C06HQ9TKL10/p1736962346283219)\n>\n> It seems like it only works for e2e and not component tests? Or there is other configs required to make it work but unsure that direction there. OR you have to opt out of the inferred target plugin and use the OG executor when doing component tests?\n>\n> cc @jason @leosvel\n>\n> \\[January 15th, 2025 9:32 AM\\] jordan.powell: <@U02K5NR6EMN> I'm trying to work on adding Component Testing inside of SXM but i'm running into a limitation with implementing it using inferred. The problem i'm having is we have a bunch of libs that need a `devServerTarget`. As far as I can tell their is no other way to pass this value to Nx outside the `project.json`. Ideally we could do one of the following:\n>\n> • Add it to `cypress.config.ts` similar to `ciWebServerCommand` \n> • Add a global `devServerTarget` in the options of the `@nx/cypress` plugin in `nx.json`\n> • Or pass it as an arg like `nx run {projectName}:component-test --devServerTarget={myTarget}`",
