    "description": "After running some migration generators (I've reproduced it with the ESLint and the WIP Jest, haven't tried the rest), the project graph doesn't infer the new task and running the task errors with `Cannot find configuration for task app1:lint`. Running without the daemon or running `nx reset` fixes it, so it should be a daemon/file watcher issue.\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n\n```bash\nNX_ADD_PLUGINS=false npx -y create-nx-workspace@canary --nx-cloud=skip --pm=pnpm foo\n\n NX   Let's create a new workspace [https://nx.dev/getting-started/intro]\n\n✔ Which stack do you want to use? · react\n✔ What framework would you like to use? · none\n✔ Integrated monorepo, or standalone project? · integrated\n✔ Application name · app1\n✔ Which bundler would you like to use? · vite\n✔ Test runner to use for end to end (E2E) tests · playwright\n✔ Default stylesheet format · css\n\n NX   Creating your v19.4.0-canary.20240615-f431d0a workspace.\n\n✔ Installing dependencies with pnpm\n✔ Successfully created the workspace: foo.\n\n—————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————\n\n\n NX   First time using Nx? Check out this interactive Nx tutorial.\n\nhttps://nx.dev/react-tutorial/1-code-generation\n```\n\n```\n❯ pnpm nx g @nx/eslint:convert-to-inferred --project app1\n\n NX  Generating @nx/eslint:convert-to-inferred\n\nUPDATE apps/app1/project.json\nUPDATE nx.json\n```\n\n```\n❯ pnpm nx lint app1\n\n NX   Cannot find configuration for task app1:lint\n\nPass --verbose to see the stacktrace.\n```\n\n### Daemon Logs\n\n```plaintext\n[NX Daemon Server] - 2024-06-17T15:47:31.822Z - Established a connection. Number of open connections: 3\n[NX Daemon Server] - 2024-06-17T15:47:31.823Z - Closed a connection. Number of open connections: 2\n[NX Daemon Server] - 2024-06-17T15:47:31.823Z - Established a connection. Number of open connections: 3\n[NX Daemon Se